    "created_at": "2015-05-31T05:01:45Z",
    "updated_at": "2015-05-31T05:01:45Z",
    "body": "I would also use something other than LocalStorage for your case. Unsure what limitations Electron imposes or lifts on it but I know in web development it has roughly a 5mb cap in most browsers. And you can only query by key name. There are some libraries online to improve on this but it would make sense to use something that naturally has the functionality. If you are saving, say, application options LocalStorage is a great option.\n"
  },
