    "created_at": "2016-05-26T07:43:10Z",
    "updated_at": "2016-05-26T07:43:10Z",
    "body": "local storage is loosing its values when closing the window. Is there something that I need to do to make it persistent? I am using **localStorage** from my angular app services.\n\n```\n\nmyAppServices.service('localStorageService', [function () {\n\n    /// userdetails\n    this.setUserDetailsGoogle = function (userDetailsGoogle) {\n\n        if (userDetailsGoogle === undefined) {\n            return false\n        }\n\n        localStorage.userDetailsGoogle = JSON.stringify(userDetailsGoogle);\n        return true;\n    };\n\n    this.getUserDetailsGoogle = function () {\n        if (localStorage.userDetailsGoogle === undefined) {\n            return null;\n        }\n\n        return JSON.parse(localStorage.userDetailsGoogle);\n    };\n\n\n    /// googleauth details\n    this.setOauthDetailsGoogle = function (oauthDetailsGoogle) {\n\n        if (oauthDetailsGoogle === undefined) {\n            return false;\n        }\n\n        localStorage.oauthDetailsGoogle = JSON.stringify(oauthDetailsGoogle);\n        return true;\n    }\n\n    this.getOauthDetailsGoogle = function () {\n        if (localStorage.oauthDetailsGoogle === undefined) {\n            return null;\n        }\n\n        return JSON.parse(localStorage.oauthDetailsGoogle);\n    };\n\n    return this;\n}]);\n```\n"
